question: Format answer for: Regarding patient 'CII-3' from family 'Family C': What is the pathogenicity classification for the third mutation?
context:
Information not found.

The document states that "Patients carrying the p.D620N mutation did not have any other variants in all exons of VPS35" (Page 3). Patient CII-3 is one of the patients identified with the p.D620N mutation. The study screened for 7 reported nonsynonymous variants of VPS35, and only p.D620N was found in the affected patients, including CII-3. There is no mention of a "third mutation" for patient CII-3.
